    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="671"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890 F. 154A/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 510</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-15">November 15,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State transmits copies of correspondence exchanged between the
                    Chief of the Division of Near Eastern Affairs and Mr. K. S. Twitchell, of 3
                    Handy Court, Burlington, Vermont, who has recently returned to this country from
                    Saudi Arabia.</p>
                <p>The American Minister is requested to inform the Saudi Arabian Government through
                    the appropriate channel that his Government will be pleased to cooperate with
                    the Saudi Arabian Government with a view to facilitating the obtainment of the
                    services of American road engineers when they may be desired.</p>
                <pb facs="0661" n="653" xml:id="pg_653"/>
                <p>When communicating with the Saudi Arabian Government the Minister may make
                    available a copy of the enclosed letter from Mr. Twitchell.<note n="38"
                        xml:id="d671fn38">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>. Reply of the Chief of the Division of Near
                        Eastern Affairs, dated November 15, 1940, not printed.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
